main event: A patrolman in Norfolk, Virginia observed an unidentified flying object believed to be Venus.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 12 minutes without any change in appearance or motion, The object was identified based on its consistent characteristics with the planet Venus, Visual observation took place at ground level without optical aids, The report indicates that no physical evidence was found, The details were documented in a Project Blue Book report.
witness description: a 21-year-old patrolman from the Norfolk Police Department
